item.description:
BC2 Fastest way to C4 Buildings
This is a video of Battlefield: Bad Company 2, demonstrating the quickest way to collapse a building using C4. Generally useful if you want to destroy MCOMs, or just piss your teammates off! I probably could have taught you guys this in 20 seconds but ... you know... whatever. Why perpendicular walls? Well it seems that C4s have a high Z axis blast radius but a low X axis one, so putting the C4 sideways I guess blows more of the walls. I hope you find usefulness within all this uselessness of a video.

item.title: Plum High School Pittsburgh Penguins Lipdub
item.description:
Plum High School Pittsburgh Penguins Lipdub
On April 1, 2010 the Television Production students at Plum High School and a few of their friends made a lipdub tribute video about the Pittsburgh Penguins. Over 100 students came to school on Thursday night for the filming. It took approximately two hours to set up, and another hour to film. We have watched several lipdub videos on youtube, and not one of them has had a theme, which is why we went with the Pittsburgh Penguins theme. After debating about several songs to use, the students and I kept on coming back to "I Got a Feelin" by the Black Eyed Peas(which we give credit to them for writing and singing a spectacular song) which was done spectacularly by the students from the University of Montreal. Hopefully you will like ours and go Pens! DISCLAIMER: In the beginning of this video we mean no disrespect with the "throwing" of the Lemieux and Jagr jerseys. We simply wanted to show the transition of great players. We have all the respect in the world for ever past or present player of the Penguins **We do not own the song used in this video** **Music Credit: The Black Eyed Peas "I Gotta Feeling"**
